text: Skylab was the first space station launched into orbit by the United States. Skylab may also refer to: *Skylab (band), a musical outfit formed in 1993 *Skylab, a tower structure at Amundsen–Scott South Pole Station *Rogério Skylab, Brazilian artist **Skylab (album), a 1999 album by Rogério Skylab ==See also== *Skylab 1, the unmanned launch of Skylab *Skylab 2, the first crewed mission to Skylab *Skylab II, a proposed lunar space station named in homage to Skylab *Skylab 3, the second crewed mission to Skylab *Skylab 4, the third and last crewed mission to Skylab *Skylab B, a backup Skylab station, proposed for a second launch but never used *Skylab Rescue, a contingency mission for a stranded Skylab crew, never needed *Skylab IX, a live album by Rogério Skylab *Skylab One (disambiguation) *Skylab Two (disambiguation) *Skylab Three (disambiguation) *Skylab Four (disambiguation)
title: Skylab (disambiguation)
